-- GM sees global industry sales growth of 2.5 percent
-- 
-- Wed Jul 23, 2008 11:09am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/07/23/us-gm-sales-growth-idUSN2346665020080723

 

 DETROIT  (Reuters) - General Motors Corp ( GM.N ) said on Wednesday that it expects global auto industry sales to grow 2.5 percent to 72 million vehicles in 2008, driven by sales increases in emerging markets. 

 GM earlier said its global sales fell 5 percent in the second quarter, hurt by a 20 percent decline in North America. The automaker trailed  Japanese rival Toyota Motor Corp( 7203.T ) in global vehicle sales decisively through the first half of the year. (Reporting by  David Bailey , editing by Gerald E. McCormick)